<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-10-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-10-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="798" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d798">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 894.001 Y8.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Ambassador of
                                    Japan</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-16">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 16, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge
                            the receipt of your note of the 11th instant, enclosing under separate
                            sealed cover, for presentation to the President of the United States, an
                            autograph letter addressed to him by His Majesty the Emperor of Japan,
                            announcing the lamented demise of His Majesty the late Emperor, and the
                            consequent accession to the Throne of His Majesty the present
                            Emperor.</p>
                        <p>In reply I have the honor to inform you that the Imperial communication
                            has been laid before the President, whose reply will be delivered
                            through the American Ambassador at Tokyo.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>